               <code>
                  <coding>
                     <system value="http://loinc.org"/>
                     <code value="8648-8"/>
                     <display value="Hospital Course"/>
                  </coding>
               </code>
               <text>
                  <status value="generated"/>
                  <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Dear colleague, we are reporting on the above-named 61-year-old male patient who was under our inpatient care from 03.08.2015 to 08.08.2015 due to polysubstance dependence. Upon admission, the patient presented with signs of acute withdrawal and chronic multiple substance misuse. Comprehensive diagnostic assessment included structured psychiatric evaluation, laboratory screening, and physical examination confirming dependence syndrome involving multiple substances. During the inpatient stay, medically supervised detoxification was initiated with pharmacological withdrawal management using benzodiazepines and supportive medication. Motivational counselling sessions were conducted and a referral to an outpatient addiction treatment programme was arranged. The patient was discharged in a stabilised condition, cooperative and motivated for continued abstinence-oriented therapy. We recommend close follow-up, ongoing psychosocial support and outpatient addiction counselling. Please do not hesitate to contact us should any questions arise.</div>
               </text>
